President Barack Obama has proclaimed October 6-12, 2013 as Fire Prevention Week in the United States. In his proclamation, he acknowledges that fires cause more American deaths than any other natural disasters and have devastating effects on families and communities. The President pays tribute to the brave firefighters who put their lives on the line to save others and emphasizes the importance of fire prevention measures. He encourages Americans to be cautious while cooking, using electrical appliances, and heating their homes, as well as to install smoke detectors and develop and practice evacuation plans. The President also calls on Americans to participate in fire prevention programs and activities and honor fallen firefighters.